column1: Uchi////Rolls here are nothing too special
column2: but the ones on the Sake Social menu are a pretty great deal
column3: and are good to fill you up. The "ham and eggs"
column4: a pork belly roll served with a mustard dipping sauce
column5: off of the standard menu is a little pricey
column6: but a pretty unique and delicious roll worth trying at least once. I also got to sample both the dayboat scallop and foie gras nigiri; both were some of the most delicious bites of the entire dinner. Though nigiri here are a tad small
column7: splurging for the foie piece is definitely worth it if you can afford it.
